After reading all the rants and raves, I FINALLY managed to get my butt down to Pop Up Pizza.
A vegan friend of mine recently blogged about their vegan pizza by the slice and I wanted to champion the cause.
When we arrived they didn't have a vegan pizza made - and I didn't want them to go to the trouble of making one just so I could have a single slice, so I went with a slice of their standard veggie.
The service was super friendly and I instantly liked the staff.
One popped our slices in the oven while we paid, another popped them out - maybe a little too soon.
Our slices weren't hot enough - the potatoes on my slice were thick enough to still be cold...but who doesn't like cold pizza?
I still really loved the crunchiness of the crust and the flavor of their sauce is way above average and kind of sweet.
We took up their table space chatting with friends from out-of-town for quite a while.
I would have given them three stars - but the guys are so nice - they even asked me if I wanted to try a vegan slice when they had one ready.
I was already sated with my slice of veggie - but total props for offering!
Still looking forward to trying the vegan!

