We got delivery again tonight, and it was super fast!
We went with a half cheese half pepperoni pie, the garden salad, and 10 buffalo wings.
The two of us barely ate half!
The wings were big and cooked just right, and though I was not expecting a breading they were crispy and delicious.
The pizza was perfect, one of the best NY style pies you will find in town without a doubt.
The salad was the show stopper though!
Roasted artichoke hearts, shredded parmesan, grape tomatoes, kalamata olives, thin and lightly applied onion, crisp romaine, all dressed with a basic Italian that reminded me why I love Italian dressing.
I could have just eaten that and been happy, but it was honestly big enough for the two of us to share as our side.
Best pizza option downtown, folks.
Just wish they'd switch to Coca Cola products!

The Plaza is quickly turning into my favorite place to be a degenerate.
I love the new William Hill Sportsbook and they have plenty of high tops, so you can eat a hot slice of Pop Up Pizza while enjoying the NBA Finals, all for less than $20.
Score!
That being said....
I'm going to keep the 5-stars for Pop Up but my second visit here was a real downer.
It wasn't bad, I just had a really good first visit but I don't think I like this place as much as my first review leads you to believe.
I got a slice of the Goodman (Mozzarella, caramelized onions,roasted mushrooms, spinach, and red potato) and it was not good.
At all.
There's thick slices of potato on the pizza.
WTF?
I don't know if they're starting to skimp on the topping, but I averaged about half a spinach leaf per slice.
It's just a bland, yucky pizza.
Next was a slice of the White Chapel (White pie with mozzarella and ricotta cheese, roasted red bell peppers and Italian sausage).
It was a decent white pie, but really, nothing special.
I can name a handful of places that do white pizza so much better.
The lack of sauce makes it bland.
**In conclusion, order the Main St. (best pepperoni in Las Vegas, if not the world), the Newport and the Soho (vegan pizza).
Chow that baby down while watching your favorite sports team.
Then if you want some more protein, walk over to the other side of the casino to get some chicken wings from Zaba's.
They have some awesome wings for $1 a piece.
Throw back a cold one and enjoy.
**  This is Vegas living right here, baby.

